excerpt: Futuristic museum with exhibitions of modern & contemporary art, fashion, design & local history.
detail_description: The Groninger Museum in Groningen, Netherlands is a must-see destination for art enthusiasts. The museum's modern and contemporary art, fashion, design, and local history exhibitions are housed in a strikingly colorful building designed by renowned architect Alessandro Mendini. Opened in 1994, the museum's unique exterior on a small island surrounded by canals sets it apart. Inside, visitors can admire masterpieces from Dutch and international artists.
name: Groninger Museum

excerpt: Gothic church with a Baroque organ & a tower that can be climbed for panoramic views, plus tours.
detail_description: Martinitoren, also known as Martini Tower, is a Gothic church with a Baroque organ and a towering structure that offers panoramic views of Groningen. Named after the city's patron saint, St. Martin, this historical tower has stood for over five centuries. Referred to as "d'Olle Grieze" by locals due to its weather-beaten sandstone color, it stands at an impressive 97 meters high.
name: Martini Tower

excerpt: Historic, Renaissance-style garden with sections for herbs & roses, plus a cafe serving sandwiches.
detail_description: The Prinsentuin, also known as the Prince's Garden, is a historic Renaissance-style garden situated in Groningen, Netherlands. Dating back to the early 17th century and located behind the Prinsenhof, this meticulously maintained garden boasts elegant flowerbeds, carefully designed hedges, and a striking sundial. Visitors are captivated by its romantic rose garden and the serene ambiance created by lush greenery.
name: Prinsentuin

excerpt: City park beside a long lake, with paths & a bandstand, plus a cafe in a circular 1930 pavilion.
detail_description: Noorderplantsoen Park is a must-see attraction in Groningen, offering splendid natural views and a serene atmosphere. This English-style park features charming canals, lush greenery, and serene ponds, providing a perfect setting for leisurely strolls or relaxation. It also serves as a lively venue for events like the Noorderzon Festival. The park offers facilities such as benches, seating areas, and a circular 1930 pavilion housing a cafe.
name: Noorderplantsoen

detail_description: Forum Groningen is a game-changer, offering a whole new level of cool with its rooftop views and diverse attractions. The modern library spreads its book collection across different themed floors, creating unique atmospheres in each space. Visitors can enjoy movies at the cinema, explore a photo exhibition, and learn about the city's history. The building also houses Story World museum and offers stunning city views from the top.
name: Forum Groningen

excerpt: Historic church with a grand Baroque organ & open for conferences, cultural evenings & tours.
name: Martini Church

excerpt: Opened in 1932, this maritime museum focuses on local history, shipbuilding & shipping.
detail_description: The Noordelijk Scheepvaartmuseum, located in Groningen, Netherlands, is a captivating maritime museum that delves into the rich history of shipbuilding and shipping in the northern region. Housed in two historic buildings, visitors can embark on an engaging journey through 18 rooms filled with exhibits such as intricately carved replicas of historical landmarks and detailed models showcasing local shipyards' operations over the centuries.
name: Noordelijk Scheepvaartmuseum

detail_description: Vismarkt is a bustling square in Groningen, known for its vibrant atmosphere and variety of attractions. It's a popular spot to conclude the day with live jazzy lounge music, drinks, and snacks at Cappuvino on Saturdays. The area surrounding Vismarkt is filled with lively bars and restaurants, making it an ideal location to experience Groningen's nightlife.
name: Vismarkt

detail_description: Grote Markt is a newly opened cafe/restaurant located in a distinctive building at the heart of the historic city square, de Grote Markt. Offering a prime location and rich historical surroundings, it provides visitors with an ideal spot to enjoy delicious food and drinks.
name: Grote Markt

excerpt: Groningen is a city in the northern Netherlands. Its central Grote Markt square is home to the centuries-old Martinitoren clock tower. The adjoining Martinikerk is a large Gothic church with frescoes and a baroque organ. Set on a canal, the futuristic Groninger Museum showcases modern and contemporary art, plus ceramics. The Northern Maritime Museum traces the history of shipbuilding and shipping in the region.
detail_description: Groningen, a city in the northern Netherlands, is known for its historical landmarks such as the Martinitoren clock tower and the Martinikerk Gothic church. The Groninger Museum showcases modern art and ceramics while the Northern Maritime Museum delves into the region's shipbuilding history. In addition to its rich cultural offerings, Groningen boasts a diverse culinary scene with a variety of Asian restaurants like Cho Fah eathai and Thai Jasmine Authentiek Thais Restaurant.
name: Groningen

excerpt: Long-established museum with a science focus, featuring medical specimens & anatomical models.
detail_description: The University Museum in Groningen is a long-established institution with a strong focus on science and nature. It houses an extensive collection that brings together elements of nature, culture, and science. Visitors can explore medical specimens, anatomical models, psychological objects, and diverse exhibits ranging from flowers and seeds to the world's first electromagnetic car. The museum also offers interactive experiences for children, such as VR expeditions and craft activities.
name: University Museum
address: Oude Kijk in Het Jatstraat 7A, 9712 EA Groningen, Netherlands

excerpt: Enduring botanical garden with 20 hectares of themed areas, including a Chinese plot & teahouse.
detail_description: Haren Hortus Botanicus is a historic and expansive botanical garden located near Groningen, Netherlands. Established in 1626, it covers 20 hectares and features various themed areas, including a unique Chinese Ming garden that is unparalleled in Europe. Visitors can explore the serene natural park just outside the bustling city center and immerse themselves in the tranquility of its surroundings.
name: Haren Hortus Botanicus

detail_description: Wall House #2, also known as the Bye House, is a striking post-modernist structure designed by American architect John Quentin Hejduk. It is managed by the Groninger Museum and stands out as an iconic architectural gem. The building was conceptualized in the 1970s as a deconstruction and constructed without practical compromises thirty years later. Its design expresses pure forms of concepts like 'wall', 'room', and 'entrance'.
name: Wall House # 2

detail_description: Located in the heart of Groningen, the Stadspark, also known as City Park, is a charming and expansive 135-acre park that attracts locals and tourists alike. With its lush greenery, meandering pathways, and diverse recreational facilities, it offers a serene retreat from the urban hustle and bustle. Whether you're seeking outdoor activities or simply want to relax amidst nature, this park provides an ideal setting for leisurely pursuits.
name: Stadspark

detail_description: Het Goudkantoor, also known as the Gold Office, is a historic monument in Groningen that dates back to 1635. This impressive building served as a tax office during the Golden Dutch Age and has survived significant historical events, including being saved from destruction during World War II. The interior of Het Goudkantoor is described as cozy and reminiscent of an old tavern, making it a recommended stop for visitors interested in history and architecture.
name: Het Goudkantoor

excerpt: Small, nostalgic museum exhibiting an extensive collection of vintage Dutch comic books.
name: Het Nederlands Stripmuseum

excerpt: Vibrant destination with a warm ambiance & a terrace dishing up light bites & hearty fare.
detail_description: De Drie Gezusters is a lively destination with a cozy atmosphere and an outdoor terrace offering a variety of light bites and hearty dishes. It's one of the top dining spots in Groningen, along with other popular restaurants like Gustatio and Mr. Mofongo. The restaurant is known for its vibrant ambiance and delicious food, making it a must-visit for anyone looking to experience the best flavors in the area.
name: De Drie Gezusters

excerpt: Prestigious university with around 25,000 students studying a wide range of subjects.
detail_description: The University of Groningen, located in the Netherlands, is a prestigious institution with a rich history dating back to the 16th century. Its campus features historic buildings, including the ornate Academia building, and welcomes around 25,000 students across various disciplines. Joining a guided tour offers insight into the university's impact on the city and its old-world charm.
name: University of Groningen

detail_description: Brasserie Prinsenhof is a historic 4-star hotel with two restaurants, including Restaurant Nassau for a refined dining experience and Brasserie Prinsenhof offering breakfast, lunch, dinner, high tea, and drinks. The former bedroom of the stadholder has been transformed into Restaurant Het Prinsenhof, providing a grand setting overlooking the beautiful Prinsentuin.
name: Brasserie Prinsenhof

detail_description: If you're a live music enthusiast, Vera is an absolute must-visit in Groningen. This alternative venue has a rich history of hosting iconic artists before they skyrocketed to fame, including legends like U2 and Nirvana. Since its inception in 1980, Vera has been the heartbeat of the local music scene, regularly featuring performances that draw enthusiastic crowds eager to enjoy diverse genres. The atmosphere is electric as you soak in the sounds from both emerging talents and established acts alike.
name: Vera
Academiegebouw
address: University of Groningen, Broerstraat 5, 9712 CP Groningen, Netherlands

excerpt: Museum devoted to the history of graphic design, printing & bookbinding, with various workshops.
detail_description: Located in Groningen, Netherlands, the Grafisch Museum Groningen (GRID) is a captivating museum dedicated to the history of graphic design, printing, and bookbinding. Visitors can immerse themselves in various exhibitions showcasing traditional printing presses, typefaces, and graphic works. The museum offers interactive workshops and demonstrations where guests can explore different aspects of graphic arts.
name: Grafisch Museum Groningen

detail_description: Bax Bier is a brewery and tasting room located just outside the city center, offering tours and beer tastings from Wednesday to Sunday. The brewery provides a picturesque setting with tables along the water, making it an ideal spot to enjoy a drink on sunny days. Visitors can sign up for a tour of the brewery and sample some of their limited edition beers. The tasting flight offers four 15cl beers for a set price, allowing guests to try different varieties.
name: Bax Bier

detail_description: Geertruidsgasthuis, located in the heart of Groningen, Netherlands, is a historic building with a rich past. Originally serving as a medieval hospital, it has been transformed into a restaurant and cultural center. The site attracts visitors interested in delving into Groningen's history and exploring its present-day offerings.
name: Geertruidsgasthuis

detail_description: Reitdiephaven is a picturesque harbor on the outskirts of the city, known for its charming and photogenic houses. These unique dwellings draw inspiration from both Scandinavian and Dutch Caribbean architecture, creating a distinctive and colorful row of homes situated on four separate piers. Not only are these houses visually striking, but they are also designed to be fully waterproof, adding to their allure.
name: Reitdiephaven

detail_description: Pernikkel is a dining spot located near the Westerhaven shopping area, making it an ideal place for a post-shopping meal. The restaurant offers an ever-changing menu with generous portions, ensuring that diners will always find something new and satisfying to enjoy. With its exciting culinary offerings, Pernikkel promises a delightful dining experience for visitors in Groningen.
name: Pernikkel

excerpt: Historic Grote Markt fans out from its bustling namesake square, home to ancient Gothic churches, the striking city hall and a thrice-weekly food market. Al fresco cafes, fashionable boutiques and apartments in century-old buildings line the streets. The leafy Martinikerkhof park contains national monuments, while Forum Groningen features the Storyworld interactive museum and a rooftop deck with panoramic city views.
detail_description: Grote Markt, also known as the Great Market Square, is a historic and bustling square located in Groningen, Netherlands. The square is surrounded by ancient Gothic churches, including the iconic Martinitoren and Martinikerk. It is also home to the striking city hall and hosts a lively food market three times a week. The area features al fresco cafes, trendy boutiques, and apartments housed in century-old buildings.
name: Grote Markt

excerpt: Chill, airy stop dishing out global comfort cuisine, plus wine & cocktails.
detail_description: Mr. Mofongo is a timeless restaurant that has been serving traditional Dutch cuisine since 1996. Located in Groningen, Netherlands, this brown cafe offers a cozy and airy atmosphere where guests can enjoy global comfort cuisine along with a selection of wine and cocktails. The menu features heart-warming stamppotten (stews) made with homemade ingredients, providing a taste of authentic flavors. With its reputation for delicious food and welcoming ambiance, Mr.
name: Mr. Mofongo

detail_description: Nestled in the bustling heart of Groningen, the Martinikerkhof is a serene green haven that invites visitors to unwind amidst its tranquil surroundings. With roots tracing back to the Middle Ages, this charming park was once a cemetery and has evolved over time, even serving as a parking area during the 70s and 80s. Today, it stands as an ideal retreat for those seeking a peaceful escape from city life or simply looking for a lovely spot to enjoy lunch outdoors.
name: Martinikerkhof

detail_description: De Oosterpoort is a beautiful venue that hosts various events, from music performances to art shows. Guests can enjoy delicious dinner options before the start of events and soak in the atmospheric ambiance. However, some visitors have noted issues with the air conditioning blowing cold air during performances. Despite this, the venue's large hall offers both standing and seating arrangements for attendees.
name: De Oosterpoort

detail_description: Storyworld is a new museum that offers an interactive and engaging experience for visitors interested in the creation of manga, animation, and video games. The displays are designed to provide insight into the development of these art forms, with a focus on storytelling. Visitors can explore hand-drawn sketches and drawings by artists, gaining a unique perspective on the creative process. While some may find the abundance of artwork overwhelming, the interactive installations and games are highlighted as innovative and enjoyable.
name: Storyworld

detail_description: Hoge der A is located in a vibrant student city with a rich history dating back to 1040. The area is home to several universities and offers a buzzing nightlife, charming squares filled with diverse dining options, and an abundance of historical sites. Groningen's significance as a hub for commerce grew as trading expanded through the northeastern sea, leading to the development of numerous waterways and canals throughout the city.
name: Hoge der A

detail_description: Groningen's red light district, located on Nieuwestad between Schoolholm and Folkingestraat, offers a more low-key experience compared to the famous one in Amsterdam. It caters primarily to actual customers rather than tourists seeking excitement. The area is known for providing good service at reasonable prices and also features ladyboys.
name: Red light district Groningen

detail_description: Brouwerij Martinus is a craft brewery located in Groningen, Netherlands. Established in 2016, it has gained a reputation for its exceptional craft beers crafted on-site using traditional methods and locally sourced ingredients. The brewery is housed in an old printing company transformed into a cozy bar and restaurant across three floors. Visitors can enjoy a variety of craft beers while learning about the brewery's story from the friendly and informative staff.
name: Brouwerij Martinus

detail_description: Station Groningen, also known as Groningen Central Station, is the primary railway station in the city of Groningen, Netherlands. Situated in the city center, it serves as a vital transportation hub connecting Groningen to various cities within the country and beyond. The station boasts a stunning interior reminiscent of a royal palace's hall and offers a range of shops, dining options, and clean facilities including spacious bicycle parking. Its proximity to the city center makes it easily accessible for travelers arriving by train.
name: Station Groningen

detail_description: The "A Bridge Too Far Tour" offers a captivating experience with an engaging guide who keeps visitors interested from start to finish. Participants can expect to learn a lot during the tour and enjoy a worthwhile lunch at noon. The "Battlefield Tour Delfzijl Pocket" provides an opportunity to discover new insights and join afternoon tours during the Day of the Wadden Sea.
name: Battlefield Tours

detail_description: The Stichting Folkingestraat Synagoge, also known as the Folkingestraat Synagogue Foundation, is a historic synagogue located in Groningen, Netherlands. The building dates back to the 19th century and is celebrated for its remarkable architecture and significant history. While it no longer hosts regular religious services, it remains an important site for understanding both the Jewish faith and the history of the Jewish community in Groningen.
name: Stichting Folkingestraat Synagoge

detail_description: Akerk, also known as Aa Church, is a historic and iconic building located in the city center of Groningen, Netherlands. Dating back to the 12th century, this Gothic-style church boasts impressive architecture and a rich history. While it no longer holds regular religious services, it has been repurposed for cultural events and concerts. The church is named after the river 'AA' and offers visitors the chance to explore its beautiful interior with an impressive organ.
name: Akerk

detail_description: As you continue your leisurely stroll through Groningen, be sure to include a visit to Korenbeurs, Akerkhof, and the historic Der Aa Kerk. The church is a remarkable monument that has stood since the 1200s, offering an awe-inspiring glimpse into centuries of history and artistry. It's truly fascinating to witness such enduring cultural treasures in person.
name: Korenbeurs

excerpt: Modern gallery established in 1980 with a focus on documentary photography exhibitions.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of the photography scene, the Noorderlicht Photography Foundation has been a beacon for documentary photography since its inception in 1980. This charming gallery offers an intimate exhibition space where stunning visuals take center stage, complemented by a team of exceptionally friendly and knowledgeable staff. Currently showcasing an impressive collection by Ruben Terlou that delves into China, visitors can enjoy not only captivating photographs but also engaging videos that enhance the viewing experience.
name: Noorderlicht Photography Foundation

excerpt: Independent art gallery showcasing the vibrant paintings of Dutch artist Erik Zwezerijnen.
detail_description: Art Gallery Erik Zwezerijnen is an independent establishment that displays the vibrant artworks created by Dutch painter Erik Zwezerijnen. For those interested in exploring Groningen's art scene, it is recommended to take note of the gallery's opening hours. In the event of no staff being present, a contact number can be found on the door. It is highly recommended to visit this gallery and appreciate the exceptional artwork on display.
name: Art Gallery Erik Zwezerijnen

detail_description: Galerie MooiMan, one of the two male art galleries worldwide, is a must-visit if you're in the vicinity. With regular new exhibitions and an extensive collection of art available for purchase, this gallery offers a unique experience to all visitors. The establishment is managed by two knowledgeable owners who are passionate about discussing the artwork on display and promoting upcoming artists in the area. It's a place where people from diverse backgrounds can come together and appreciate art in a fresh way.
name: Galerie MooiMan male-art

detail_description: Mezrab offers a charming performance space at their upstairs bar, complete with impressive lighting and acoustics. The staff and ambiance are welcoming, creating a friendly atmosphere for patrons. Smokers can enjoy the balcony which comfortably accommodates up to eight people. In January 2023, Grand Pillow Society showcased captivating narratives intertwined with music, accompanied by delightful socks as souvenirs. Their storytelling events have gained commendable reputation for excellence. Special thanks to Tes for providing exceptional service.
name: Grand Theatre

detail_description: The Jozef Isralsmonument is a work of art that commemorates the renowned sculptor Jozef Israls. This sculpture stands as a tribute to his contributions to the artistic world and serves as a lasting symbol of his influence. The monument showcases Israls' innovative style and mastery, capturing his creative spirit through intricate details and refined craftsmanship.
name: Jozef Isralsmonument

detail_description: Trampolinepark Jumpstyle Heerenveen is a fantastic destination for families and groups seeking an exhilarating jumping experience. The park offers special birthday programs, so be sure to book in advance. While the staff are friendly and well-trained, some visitors noted that there are quite a few rules to follow and not all facilities may be accessible. Nevertheless, it's a top-notch place for kids to have an awesome time jumping around.
name: Trampolinepark Jumpstyle Heerenveen
